\chapter{Model Description}
\label{ch:model_description}

\lettrine[lines=2]{T}{his chapter} presents a detailed description of the agent-based model architecture, including the spatial environment, the 18 agent types and their class hierarchy, the effect system for paracrine signaling, movement mechanics, and terminal conditions that determine simulation outcomes.

% ============================================================================
\section{Overview}
\label{sec:md_overview}
% ============================================================================

\subsection{Spatial Environment}
\label{subsec:md_spatial}

The simulation uses a 3D discrete grid with dimensions computed from tumor volume, featuring sticky borders and multiple agent occupancy. A continuous glucose concentration field overlays the discrete grid.

\subsection{Agent Types}
\label{subsec:md_agent_types}

The model comprises 18 distinct agent types, each identified by an integer ID in the \texttt{AgentType} enumeration. Table~\ref{tab:agent_types} lists all agent types with their IDs and functional categories.

